      <review>
         <snippet>Keith -- a consistent hit-maker who wrote the controversial 9/11 song "Courtesy of the Red, White and Blue" -- has a future in movies if he wants it. Hopefully, they'll be better ones than this.</snippet>
         <url>http://metromix.chicagotribune.com/movies/mmx-060908-movies-review-bridges,0,5045408.story?coll=mmx-movies_top_heds</url>
         <critic>Michael Wilmington</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>The Country Music Channel's first foray into feature filmmaking is sickly sweet and thoroughly predictable, and woefully underuses veterans Harper and Reynolds, but it features some stirring performances, including BeBe Winans and Willie Nelson dueting on "The Uncloudy Day."</snippet>
         <url>http://online.tvguide.com/newsearch/detail.aspx?tvobjectid=283145&amp;more=ucmoviereview</url>
         <critic>Maitland McDonagh</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>Get the soundtrack; wait for the movie to come to CMT.</snippet>
