         <critic>David Hiltbrand</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>It's obviously intended as a star vehicle, but Broken Bridges turns out to be a rattletrap jalopy for country music performer Toby Keith.</snippet>
         <url>http://www.variety.com/review/VE1117931681?categoryid=31&amp;cs=1</url>
         <critic>Joe Leydon</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>Keith is an awkward, galumphing presence, but he's more fun to watch than Kelly Preston as the girl's uptight mother.</snippet>
         <url>http://onfilm.chicagoreader.com/movies/briefs/30220_BROKEN_BRIDGES.html</url>
         <critic>J.R. Jones</critic>
      </review>
      <review>
         <snippet>Country Music Television's answer to "Elizabethtown."</snippet>
